{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:35:37.837Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reproducibility"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in ML is the ability to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "get the same results any time, anywhere"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", whether you run the experiment yourself, a teammate runs it, or you run it again months later. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Seeds"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are the key mechanism for achieving this: by setting "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "random seeds"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to fixed values, you lock in the randomness in your training process, making experiments deterministic and reproducible."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition of reproducibility:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " “Reproducibility in machine learning experiments means that you or someone else can run the same code with the same data and get the same results.”"}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Reproducibility & Seeds — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What reproducibility means in ML Engineering"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reproducibility ensures that:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Your "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "model performance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is stable across runs"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You (or teammates) can "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "recreate a specific result"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for:"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Debugging - Deployment - Verification"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Without reproducibility, if your accuracy or predictions change every time, your system is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "not reliable"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and you can’t trust it for production."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What random seeds are"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "random seed"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is an initial value given to a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "random number generator (RNG)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that controls all randomized operations in your ML pipeline:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model weight initialization"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Data shuffling"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dropout masks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch sampling"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Augmentation randomness"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Any "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "random"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "numpy.random"}, {"type": "text", "text": " operations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When you set a seed (e.g., "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "42"}, {"type": "text", "text": "), the RNG produces the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "same sequence of random numbers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " every time, making the entire process deterministic."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example in Python:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import random\nimport torch\nimport numpy\n\n# Set seeds for reproducibility\nrandom.seed(42)\ntorch.manual_seed(42)\nnumpy.random.seed(42)\ntorch.cuda.manual_seed(42)  # GPU random"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why seeds matter for reproducibility"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Randomness in ML comes from:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weight initialization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Neural networks start with random weights"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data shuffling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Training data is shuffled each epoch"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dropout"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Random neurons are dropped during training"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch sampling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Random batches are sampled"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Augmentation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Random transformations (flips, rotations)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If you don’t fix seeds:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each run will have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "different initial weights"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different data shuffling → different batches → different training dynamics"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Results will "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vary between runs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " even with the same code and data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fixing seeds "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "locks this randomness"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", so:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The same initialization → same starting point"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same shuffling → same training batches"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same dropout → same training behavior"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same results every time"}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "“By setting random seed you lock that randomness.”"}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to achieve reproducibility (complete checklist)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reproducibility requires "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "multiple interconnected elements"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", not just seeds:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Element"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What to track/log"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Random seeds"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "random.seed()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torch.manual_seed()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "numpy.random.seed()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", GPU seeds"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Locks all randomness in the pipeline"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hyperparameters"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learning rate, batch size, layers, dropout, optimizer, scheduler"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Determines model behavior"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data version"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Exact dataset version, split ratios, preprocessing steps"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same data → same results"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Code version"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Git commit hash"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same code → same logic"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Environment"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Library versions (e.g., PyTorch 2.1, Python 3.10), GPU type, OS"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same dependencies → same behavior"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model architecture"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Architecture config, number of layers, embedding sizes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same structure → same capacity"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Artifacts"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model files, logs, visualizations, confusion matrices"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can reproduce and verify results"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key principle:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " “You stand a much better chance of reproducing a specific result if you know the exact code version, data version, parameters, and environment used.”"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practical workflow for reproducible experiments"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Set seeds at the start of training"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def set_seed(seed=42):\n    import random\n    import torch\n    import numpy as np\n    \n    random.seed(seed)\n    torch.manual_seed(seed)\n    np.random.seed(seed)\n    torch.cuda.manual_seed(seed)\n    torch.cuda.manual_seed_all(seed)  # Multi-GPU\n    torch.backends.cudnn.deterministic = True\n    torch.backends.cudnn.benchmark = False"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Log everything in experiment tracking"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "mlflow.log_param('seed', 42)\nmlflow.log_param('lr', 0.001)\nmlflow.log_param('batch_size', 32)\nmlflow.log_param('git_commit', 'abc123def')\nmlflow.log_param('torch_version', torch.__version__)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Save data version"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use data versioning tools (DVC, Git LFS, etc.)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Log the exact dataset hash/version"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. Use consistent virtual environments"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pin dependencies in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "requirements.txt"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "environment.yml"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Docker or virtualenv to lock the environment"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes that break reproducibility"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ Only setting "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torch.manual_seed()"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Missing other RNGs (numpy, random, CUDA)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fix"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Set seeds for all libraries (Python "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "random"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", numpy, PyTorch, CUDA)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ Not logging data version"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Same hyperparameters on different data → different results"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fix"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Log dataset version alongside seeds and parameters"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ Not disabling CUDA benchmarking"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CUDA's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "benchmark=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " can make operations non-deterministic"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fix"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Set "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "cudnn.deterministic = True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "cudnn.benchmark = False"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ Using infinite random seeds for every experiment"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Extreme results (too high or too low) may not be representative"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Recommended approach"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Initial exploration"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Randomly choose multiple seeds, observe variability 2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Select representative seed"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Pick one with average performance (not extreme) 3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fix that seed"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use it consistently in subsequent experiments"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs: reproducibility vs. exploration"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "While reproducibility is crucial, there’s a trade-off with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "statistical robustness"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reproducibility focus"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Fix one seed, run many experiments → results are consistent but may be biased to that seed"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exploration focus"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Run with multiple seeds → results capture variability but aren’t perfectly reproducible"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Balanced approach"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "multiple random seeds"}, {"type": "text", "text": " during initial exploration to understand variability"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pick a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "representative seed"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (average performance)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fix that seed"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for all subsequent experiments to ensure consistency"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reproducibility"}, {"type": "text", "text": " means you can run the same code with the same data and get the same results anytime, anywhere."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Random seeds"}, {"type": "text", "text": " lock all randomness in your ML pipeline (weight initialization, shuffling, dropout, augmentation), making experiments deterministic."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reproducibility requires "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "seeds + hyperparameters + data version + code version + environment + artifacts"}, {"type": "text", "text": " all tracked together."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practice: set seeds for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all RNGs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Python, numpy, PyTorch, CUDA), log data version, pin dependencies, and use Git for code versioning."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-off: use multiple seeds for initial exploration, then fix a representative seed for reproducibility in later experiments."}]}]}]}]}}